BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 210.0 750 Td (UNDERSTANDING COMBAT PTSD) Tj ET
q 0.3 G 1 w 50 742 m 562 742 l S Q
BT 0 g /F2 12 Tf 50 720 Td (WHAT IS PTSD?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 702 Td (Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder is a normal response to abnormal events.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 687 Td (Your brain is doing exactly what it was trained to do: stay alert, anticipate) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 672 Td (threats, and protect you. The problem is that these responses are now) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 657 Td (activating in situations where there is no actual danger.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 627 Td (PREVALENCE IN VETERANS:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 609 Td (- 11-20% of veterans from Iraq/Afghanistan develop PTSD) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 594 Td (- 12% of Gulf War veterans have PTSD in a given year) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 579 Td (- 15% of Vietnam veterans were diagnosed with PTSD at time of study) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 564 Td (- You are NOT alone. Millions of veterans share this experience.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 534 Td (PTSD IS NOT WEAKNESS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 516 Td (Just as a physical injury from combat requires medical treatment, a) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 501 Td (psychological injury requires care. PTSD is not a character flaw.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 486 Td (It is not cowardice. It is a wound that needs healing.) Tj ET
q 0.93 g 50 376 512 80 re f Q
